First install R, the language

add this line to the repository

deb https://cloud.r-project.org/bin/linux/ubuntu focal-cran40/

the repositories file can be find in

 /etc/apt/sources.list

Therefore just type

sudo nano  /etc/apt/sources.list

Now go to the end (shortcut: ctrl+w and then ctrl+v)

Then add the line

Save (ctrl + o and then enter) and then quit (ctrl + x)

NOW (and just now!)

sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install r-base




After that you can install r-studio server

sudo apt-get install gdebi-core
wget https://download2.rstudio.org/server/bionic/amd64/rstudio-server-1.4.1106-amd64.deb
sudo gdebi rstudio-server-1.4.1106-amd64.deb


Sudo rstudio-server status




The server will listen to 8787 port

So go to a browser and type:

http://hostname:8787

or

http://IPaddress:8787
